=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Start from the corresponding 3-hydroxycyclobutane-1-carboxylic acid; esterify (MeOH, cat. H2SO4) to give methyl 3-hydroxycyclobutane-1-carboxylate, using the stereoisomer opposite to the target at the OH-bearing center. | Step 2: Convert the alcohol to the mesylate or tosylate (MsCl or TsCl, Et3N) to form methyl 3-OMs/OTs-cyclobutane-1-carboxylate. | Step 3: Displace the sulfonate with NaN3 in DMF (SN2) to give methyl 3-azidocyclobutane-1-carboxylate with the target ring stereochemistry. | Step 4: Hydrolyze the methyl ester (LiOH/H2O or NaOH/MeOH, then acid workup) to 3-azidocyclobutane-1-carboxylic acid. | Step 5: Convert the acid to the acid chloride with SOCl2 (or (COCl)2, cat. DMF) to obtain [N-]=[N+]=N[C@@H]1C[C@@H](C(=O)Cl)C1.

